Polyus Gold, Rostelecom and Uralkali: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-03-31T20:00:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/polyus-gold-rostelecom-and-uralkali-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  slipped 0.1 percent to 1,813.59.
The dollar-denominated RTS Index added 0.4 percent to 2,044.20.  OAO Polyus Gold (PLZL RX):  Russia ’s biggest gold producer
gained 2 percent to 1,704.6 rubles on the Micex. Gold futures
climbed on the Comex in  New York  as fighting in  Libya  and
concerns about European debt spurred demand for an alternative
investment.  OAO Rostelecom (RTKM RX): Russia’s dominant long-distance
operator reported a fourth-quarter net loss attributable to
shareholders of 1.135 billion rubles ($40 million), from a
profit of 231 million rubles a year earlier. Its stock climbed
1.9 percent to 172.01 rubles.  OAO Uralkali (URKA RX): Russia’s second-biggest potash
producer is scheduled to report 2010 second-half results based
on international financial reporting standards.  Uralkali (URKA)  gained
0.1 percent to 235.13 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
